Note:
This file handles code navigation and LSP navigation integration.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process code navigation and LSP navigation integration
- Handle symbol navigation and reference navigation
- Manage navigation tracking and navigation metadata
- Process navigation communication and navigation protocol implementation

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Code navigation enables LSP navigation integration and navigation support
- Proper navigation handling ensures correct symbol and reference navigation
- Navigation support enables Runa compilation for LSP-integrated navigation handling

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Go-to-definition for variables, functions, types, and imports
- Find-references across document and workspace scope
- Document symbol outline for quick navigation
- Workspace-wide symbol search
- Hover information with type and documentation details
- Location structure for representing source positions

Dependencies:
- Imports compiler/internal/memory_safety.runa for safe memory access
- Imports compiler/internal/owned_utils.runa for heap allocation
- Imports compiler/internal/string_utils.runa for string operations
- Imports compiler/internal/collections.runa for result list management
:End Note

Import "compiler/internal/memory_safety.runa" as MemorySafety
Import "compiler/internal/owned_utils.runa" as OwnedUtils
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils
Import "compiler/internal/collections.runa" as Collections

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Navigation Data Structures
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Location structure (32 bytes total, 4 fields x 8 bytes each)
Note: Layout:
Note:   offset 0:  file_path (8 bytes) - Pointer to file path string
Note:   offset 8:  line (8 bytes) - Zero-based line number
Note:   offset 16: column (8 bytes) - Zero-based column number
Note:   offset 24: end_line (8 bytes) - Zero-based end line number (for range)

Type called "Location":
    file_path as Integer
    line as Integer
    column as Integer
    end_line as Integer
End Type

End Type

Note: SymbolInfo structure (40 bytes) for document/workspace symbol responses
Note: Layout:
Note:   offset 0:  name (8 bytes) - Pointer to symbol name string
Note:   offset 8:  kind (8 bytes) - Symbol kind constant (function, variable, type, etc.)
Note:   offset 16: location (8 bytes) - Pointer to Location structure
Note:   offset 24: container_name (8 bytes) - Pointer to containing scope name (or 0)
Note:   offset 32: detail (8 bytes) - Pointer to detail/type info string (or 0)

Type called "SymbolInfo":
    name as Integer
    kind as Integer
    location as Integer
    container_name as Integer
    detail as Integer
End Type

End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Symbol Kind Constants (matching LSP SymbolKind values)
Note: ============================================================================

Constant SYMBOL_KIND_FILE as Integer is 1
Constant SYMBOL_KIND_MODULE as Integer is 2
Constant SYMBOL_KIND_NAMESPACE as Integer is 3
Constant SYMBOL_KIND_CLASS as Integer is 5
Constant SYMBOL_KIND_METHOD as Integer is 6
Constant SYMBOL_KIND_FUNCTION as Integer is 12
Constant SYMBOL_KIND_VARIABLE as Integer is 13
Constant SYMBOL_KIND_CONSTANT as Integer is 14
Constant SYMBOL_KIND_STRING as Integer is 15
Constant SYMBOL_KIND_STRUCT as Integer is 23
Constant SYMBOL_KIND_TYPE_PARAMETER as Integer is 26

Note: Maximum results for search operations
Constant MAX_NAVIGATION_RESULTS as Integer is 512
Constant MAX_SYMBOL_RESULTS as Integer is 256

Note: Return codes
Constant NAVIGATION_SUCCESS as Integer is 0
Constant NAVIGATION_FAILED as Integer is -1
Constant NAVIGATION_NOT_FOUND as Integer is -2

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Core Navigation Operations
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "go_to_definition" takes document_text as Integer, file_path as Integer, cursor_line as Integer, cursor_col as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Navigate to the definition of the symbol at the cursor position
    Note:
    Note: Strategy:
    Note: 1. Extract the identifier at the cursor position
    Note: 2. Determine the identifier category (variable, function, type, import)
    Note: 3. Search the document (and imported files) for the definition
    Note: 4. Return a Location pointing to the definition site
    Note:
    Note: Supported definition targets:
    Note: - Variables: "Let <name> be ..." declaration
    Note: - Functions: 'Process called "<name>"' declaration
    Note: - Types: 'Type called "<name>"' declaration
    Note: - Constants: "Constant <name> as ..." declaration
    Note: - Imports: The imported file path
    Note:
    Note: Parameters:
    Note:   document_text - Pointer to full document text
    Note:   file_path - Pointer to current file path string
    Note:   cursor_line - Zero-based line number
    Note:   cursor_col - Zero-based column number
    Note:
    Note: Returns pointer to Location, or 0 if definition not found

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Extract the identifier at the cursor position
    Let ident_info be proc extract_identifier_at with document_text, cursor_line, cursor_col
    If ident_info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ident_info is a 16-byte struct: [name_ptr (8), name_len (8)]
    Let ident_name be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with ident_info, 0
    Let ident_len be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with ident_info, 8

    If ident_name is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_info
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Search the document for the definition of this identifier
    Let doc_len be proc measure_string_len from document_text
    Let definition_line be -1
    Let definition_col be 0

    Note: Search for "Let <ident> be" pattern (variable definition)
    Let var_line be proc find_let_declaration with document_text, doc_len, ident_name, ident_len
    If var_line is not equal to -1:
        Set definition_line to var_line
        Set definition_col to 4
    End If

    Note: Search for 'Process called "<ident>"' pattern (function definition)
    If definition_line is equal to -1:
        Let proc_line be proc find_process_declaration with document_text, doc_len, ident_name, ident_len
        If proc_line is not equal to -1:
            Set definition_line to proc_line
            Set definition_col to 16
        End If
    End If

    Note: Search for 'Type called "<ident>"' pattern (type definition)
    If definition_line is equal to -1:
        Let type_line be proc find_type_declaration with document_text, doc_len, ident_name, ident_len
        If type_line is not equal to -1:
            Set definition_line to type_line
            Set definition_col to 13
        End If
    End If

    Note: Search for "Constant <ident> as" pattern
    If definition_line is equal to -1:
        Let const_line be proc find_constant_declaration with document_text, doc_len, ident_name, ident_len
        If const_line is not equal to -1:
            Set definition_line to const_line
            Set definition_col to 9
        End If
    End If

    Note: Clean up identifier info
    Let dummy_free_name be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_name
    Let dummy_free_info be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_info

    If definition_line is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create and return the Location
    Let location be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 32
    If location is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dummy_fp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with location, 0, file_path
    Let dummy_line be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with location, 8, definition_line
    Let dummy_col be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with location, 16, definition_col
    Let dummy_end be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with location, 24, definition_line

    Return location
End Process

Process called "find_references" takes document_text as Integer, file_path as Integer, cursor_line as Integer, cursor_col as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Find all references to the symbol at the cursor position
    Note:
    Note: Strategy:
    Note: 1. Extract the identifier at the cursor position
    Note: 2. Scan the entire document for all occurrences of that identifier
    Note: 3. Filter to only identifier contexts (not inside strings or comments)
    Note: 4. Return an array of Location structures
    Note:
    Note: Returns pointer to result array structure (data_ptr, count, capacity), or 0

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Extract identifier at cursor
    Let ident_info be proc extract_identifier_at with document_text, cursor_line, cursor_col
    If ident_info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ident_name be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with ident_info, 0
    Let ident_len be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with ident_info, 8

    If ident_name is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_info
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate result list (24 bytes: data_ptr, count, capacity)
    Let result be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 24
    If result is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free_name be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_name
        Let dummy_free_info be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_info
        Return 0
    End If

    Let locations_array be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with MAX_NAVIGATION_RESULTS multiplied by 8
    If locations_array is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free_res be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with result
        Set dummy_free_name to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_name
        Set dummy_free_info to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_info
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dummy_data be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 0, locations_array
    Let dummy_count be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 8, 0
    Let dummy_cap be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 16, MAX_NAVIGATION_RESULTS

    Note: Scan document for all occurrences of the identifier
    Let doc_len be proc measure_string_len from document_text
    Let scan_pos be 0
    Let current_line be 0
    Let current_col be 0
    Let ref_count be 0
    Let in_comment be 0
    Let in_string be 0

    While scan_pos is less than doc_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos

        Note: Track line and column
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Set current_line to current_line plus 1
            Set current_col to 0
            Set in_comment to 0
            Set scan_pos to scan_pos plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Note: Check for comment start "Note:" (N=78, o=111, t=116, e=101, :=58)
            If ch is equal to 78:
                If scan_pos plus 4 is less than doc_len:
                    Let c1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos plus 1
                    Let c4 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos plus 4
                    If c1 is equal to 111:
                        If c4 is equal to 58:
                            Set in_comment to 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If

            Note: Toggle string tracking on quotes
            If ch is equal to 34:
                If in_comment is equal to 0:
                    If in_string is equal to 0:
                        Set in_string to 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set in_string to 0
                    End If
                End If
            End If

            Note: Check for identifier match (only in code context)
            If in_comment is equal to 0:
                If in_string is equal to 0:
                    Let first_byte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with ident_name, 0
                    If ch is equal to first_byte:
                        Note: Potential match - verify full identifier
                        Let match be proc check_identifier_match with document_text, scan_pos, doc_len, ident_name, ident_len
                        If match is equal to 1:
                            Note: Verify it's a whole word (not part of a larger identifier)
                            Let is_whole_word be proc check_word_boundary with document_text, scan_pos, ident_len, doc_len
                            If is_whole_word is equal to 1:
                                Note: Create a Location for this reference
                                If ref_count is less than MAX_NAVIGATION_RESULTS:
                                    Let loc be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 32
                                    If loc is not equal to 0:
                                        Let dummy_loc_fp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with loc, 0, file_path
                                        Let dummy_loc_ln be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with loc, 8, current_line
                                        Let dummy_loc_cl be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with loc, 16, current_col
                                        Let dummy_loc_el be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with loc, 24, current_line
                                        Let dummy_add be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with locations_array, ref_count multiplied by 8, loc
                                        Set ref_count to ref_count plus 1
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If

            Set current_col to current_col plus 1
            Set scan_pos to scan_pos plus 1
        End If
    End While

    Note: Update result count
    Let dummy_final_count be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 8, ref_count

    Set dummy_free_name to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_name
    Set dummy_free_info to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_info

    Return result
End Process

Process called "document_symbols" takes document_text as Integer, file_path as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract all symbols from the document for the outline view
    Note: Returns an array of SymbolInfo structures representing all declared
    Note: processes, types, constants, and top-level variables
    Note:
    Note: Returns pointer to result array (data_ptr, count, capacity), or 0

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate result list
    Let result be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 24
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let symbols_array be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with MAX_SYMBOL_RESULTS multiplied by 8
    If symbols_array is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with result
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dummy_data be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 0, symbols_array
    Let dummy_count be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 8, 0
    Let dummy_cap be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 16, MAX_SYMBOL_RESULTS

    Note: Scan the document line by line for declarations
    Let doc_len be proc measure_string_len from document_text
    Let scan_pos be 0
    Let current_line be 0
    Let sym_count be 0

    While scan_pos is less than doc_len:
        Note: Skip leading whitespace on the line
        Let line_start be scan_pos
        While line_start is less than doc_len:
            Let wc be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_start
            If wc is not equal to 32:
                If wc is not equal to 9:
                    Set line_start to line_start plus doc_len
                End If
            End If
            Set line_start to line_start plus 1
        End While
        If line_start is greater than doc_len:
            Set line_start to line_start minus doc_len
        End If

        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_start

        Note: Check for "Process " (P=80) - function declaration
        If ch is equal to 80:
            If line_start plus 7 is less than doc_len:
                Let c1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_start plus 1
                If c1 is equal to 114:
                    Note: Extract process name from 'Process called "<name>"'
                    Let name_ptr be proc extract_quoted_name with document_text, line_start, doc_len
                    If name_ptr is not equal to 0:
                        If sym_count is less than MAX_SYMBOL_RESULTS:
                            Let sym be proc create_symbol_info with name_ptr, SYMBOL_KIND_FUNCTION, file_path, current_line, 0
                            If sym is not equal to 0:
                                Let dummy_add be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with symbols_array, sym_count multiplied by 8, sym
                                Set sym_count to sym_count plus 1
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Note: Check for "Type " (T=84) - type declaration
        If ch is equal to 84:
            If line_start plus 4 is less than doc_len:
                Set c1 to proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_start plus 1
                If c1 is equal to 121:
                    Set name_ptr to proc extract_quoted_name with document_text, line_start, doc_len
                    If name_ptr is not equal to 0:
                        If sym_count is less than MAX_SYMBOL_RESULTS:
                            Set sym to proc create_symbol_info with name_ptr, SYMBOL_KIND_STRUCT, file_path, current_line, 0
                            If sym is not equal to 0:
                                Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with symbols_array, sym_count multiplied by 8, sym
                                Set sym_count to sym_count plus 1
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Note: Check for "Constant " (C=67) - constant declaration
        If ch is equal to 67:
            If line_start plus 8 is less than doc_len:
                Set c1 to proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_start plus 1
                If c1 is equal to 111:
                    Set name_ptr to proc extract_word_after with document_text, line_start plus 9, doc_len
                    If name_ptr is not equal to 0:
                        If sym_count is less than MAX_SYMBOL_RESULTS:
                            Set sym to proc create_symbol_info with name_ptr, SYMBOL_KIND_CONSTANT, file_path, current_line, 0
                            If sym is not equal to 0:
                                Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with symbols_array, sym_count multiplied by 8, sym
                                Set sym_count to sym_count plus 1
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Note: Check for "Import " (I=73) - import declaration
        If ch is equal to 73:
            If line_start plus 6 is less than doc_len:
                Set c1 to proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_start plus 1
                If c1 is equal to 109:
                    Set name_ptr to proc extract_quoted_string_after with document_text, line_start plus 7, doc_len
                    If name_ptr is not equal to 0:
                        If sym_count is less than MAX_SYMBOL_RESULTS:
                            Set sym to proc create_symbol_info with name_ptr, SYMBOL_KIND_MODULE, file_path, current_line, 0
                            If sym is not equal to 0:
                                Set dummy_add to proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with symbols_array, sym_count multiplied by 8, sym
                                Set sym_count to sym_count plus 1
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Note: Advance to next line
        Let next_line_scan be scan_pos
        While next_line_scan is less than doc_len:
            Let nlc be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, next_line_scan
            If nlc is equal to 10:
                Set scan_pos to next_line_scan plus 1
                Set current_line to current_line plus 1
                Set next_line_scan to doc_len
            Otherwise:
                Set next_line_scan to next_line_scan plus 1
            End If
        End While
        If next_line_scan is equal to doc_len:
            Set scan_pos to doc_len
        End If
    End While

    Let dummy_final_count be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 8, sym_count
    Return result
End Process

Process called "workspace_symbols" takes query as Integer, document_store as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Search for symbols across all open documents matching the query string
    Note:
    Note: Parameters:
    Note:   query - Pointer to search query string (can be partial)
    Note:   document_store - Pointer to hash table of open documents
    Note:
    Note: Returns pointer to result array (data_ptr, count, capacity), or 0
    Note: Delegates to document_symbols for each open document and filters by query

    If document_store is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate result list
    Let result be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 24
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let symbols_array be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with MAX_SYMBOL_RESULTS multiplied by 8
    If symbols_array is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with result
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dummy_data be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 0, symbols_array
    Let dummy_count be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 8, 0
    Let dummy_cap be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 16, MAX_SYMBOL_RESULTS

    Note: Iterate through all documents in the store
    Let store_capacity be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_store, 16
    Let buckets be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_store, 0
    Let total_symbols be 0

    Let bucket_idx be 0
    While bucket_idx is less than store_capacity:
        Let doc_entry be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with buckets, bucket_idx multiplied by 8
        If doc_entry is not equal to 0:
            Let doc_uri be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_entry, 0
            Let doc_text be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_entry, 8

            If doc_text is not equal to 0:
                Note: Get symbols from this document
                Let doc_symbols be proc document_symbols with doc_text, doc_uri
                If doc_symbols is not equal to 0:
                    Let doc_sym_count be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_symbols, 8
                    Let doc_sym_data be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_symbols, 0

                    Note: Filter symbols by query and add to workspace results
                    Let si be 0
                    While si is less than doc_sym_count:
                        Let sym_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_sym_data, si multiplied by 8
                        If sym_ptr is not equal to 0:
                            Note: Check if symbol name matches query
                            Let sym_name be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with sym_ptr, 0
                            Let matches be proc fuzzy_match_query with sym_name, query
                            If matches is equal to 1:
                                If total_symbols is less than MAX_SYMBOL_RESULTS:
                                    Let dummy_add be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with symbols_array, total_symbols multiplied by 8, sym_ptr
                                    Set total_symbols to total_symbols plus 1
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                        Set si to si plus 1
                    End While

                    Note: Free the document symbols container (but not the symbol objects we transferred)
                    Let dummy_free_arr be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with doc_sym_data
                    Let dummy_free_res be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with doc_symbols
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set bucket_idx to bucket_idx plus 1
    End While

    Let dummy_final_count be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 8, total_symbols
    Return result
End Process

Process called "hover_info" takes document_text as Integer, cursor_line as Integer, cursor_col as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get hover information for the symbol at the cursor position
    Note: Returns a string containing type information, documentation, or declaration
    Note:
    Note: The hover response includes:
    Note: - For variables: type annotation and initial value
    Note: - For functions: full signature (parameters and return type)
    Note: - For types: type structure (fields or variants)
    Note: - For constants: type and value
    Note: - For keywords: brief description
    Note:
    Note: Returns pointer to hover text string, or 0 if no hover info available

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Extract the identifier at cursor
    Let ident_info be proc extract_identifier_at with document_text, cursor_line, cursor_col
    If ident_info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ident_name be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with ident_info, 0
    Let ident_len be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with ident_info, 8

    If ident_name is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_info
        Return 0
    End If

    Let doc_len be proc measure_string_len from document_text

    Note: Check if it's a keyword first
    Let keyword_hover be proc get_keyword_hover with ident_name, ident_len
    If keyword_hover is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free_name be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_name
        Let dummy_free_info be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_info
        Return keyword_hover
    End If

    Note: Search for the declaration to build hover info
    Note: Try Process declaration first
    Let proc_line be proc find_process_declaration with document_text, doc_len, ident_name, ident_len
    If proc_line is not equal to -1:
        Note: Extract the full Process signature line for hover
        Let hover_text be proc extract_line_text with document_text, doc_len, proc_line
        Set dummy_free_name to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_name
        Set dummy_free_info to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_info
        Return hover_text
    End If

    Note: Try Type declaration
    Let type_line be proc find_type_declaration with document_text, doc_len, ident_name, ident_len
    If type_line is not equal to -1:
        Set hover_text to proc extract_line_text with document_text, doc_len, type_line
        Set dummy_free_name to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_name
        Set dummy_free_info to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_info
        Return hover_text
    End If

    Note: Try Constant declaration
    Let const_line be proc find_constant_declaration with document_text, doc_len, ident_name, ident_len
    If const_line is not equal to -1:
        Set hover_text to proc extract_line_text with document_text, doc_len, const_line
        Set dummy_free_name to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_name
        Set dummy_free_info to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_info
        Return hover_text
    End If

    Note: Try Let declaration
    Let var_line be proc find_let_declaration with document_text, doc_len, ident_name, ident_len
    If var_line is not equal to -1:
        Set hover_text to proc extract_line_text with document_text, doc_len, var_line
        Set dummy_free_name to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_name
        Set dummy_free_info to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_info
        Return hover_text
    End If

    Set dummy_free_name to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_name
    Set dummy_free_info to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ident_info
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal Helper Processes
Note: ============================================================================

Private Process called "extract_identifier_at" takes document_text as Integer, line as Integer, col as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract the identifier name at the given line and column
    Note: Returns a 16-byte struct: [name_ptr (8), name_len (8)], or 0

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Find the line offset
    Let line_offset be proc find_line_start with document_text, line

    If line_offset is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Find word boundaries around the cursor column
    Let word_start be col
    While word_start is greater than 0:
        Let prev_ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_offset plus word_start minus 1
        Let is_ident be proc is_identifier_char from prev_ch
        If is_ident is equal to 0:
            Set word_start to 0
        Otherwise:
            Set word_start to word_start minus 1
        End If
    End While

    Let doc_len be proc measure_string_len from document_text
    Let word_end be col

    While line_offset plus word_end is less than doc_len:
        Let next_ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_offset plus word_end
        Set is_ident to proc is_identifier_char from next_ch
        If is_ident is equal to 0:
            Set word_end to word_end plus doc_len
        Otherwise:
            Set word_end to word_end plus 1
        End If
    End While
    If word_end is greater than doc_len:
        Set word_end to word_end minus doc_len
    End If

    Let name_len be word_end minus word_start
    If name_len is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Copy the identifier name
    Let name_buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with name_len plus 1
    If name_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than name_len:
        Let byte_val be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_offset plus word_start plus idx
        Let dummy_cp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with name_buf, idx, byte_val
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While
    Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with name_buf, name_len, 0

    Note: Allocate result struct
    Let result be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 16
    If result is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with name_buf
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dummy_name be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 0, name_buf
    Let dummy_len be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 8, name_len

    Return result
End Process

Private Process called "find_line_start" takes document_text as Integer, target_line as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Find byte offset of the start of the given line (zero-based)

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    If target_line is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let current_line be 0
    Let offset be 0
    Let max_offset be 1048576

    While offset is less than max_offset:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, offset
        If ch is equal to 0:
            Return -1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Set current_line to current_line plus 1
            If current_line is equal to target_line:
                Return offset plus 1
            End If
        End If
        Set offset to offset plus 1
    End While

    Return -1
End Process

Private Process called "is_identifier_char" takes ch as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if character is valid in an identifier (alphanumeric or underscore)
    If ch is greater than 96:
        If ch is less than 123:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    If ch is greater than 64:
        If ch is less than 91:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    If ch is greater than 47:
        If ch is less than 58:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    If ch is equal to 95:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Private Process called "find_let_declaration" takes doc as Integer, doc_len as Integer, name as Integer, name_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Search for "Let <name> be" declaration, return line number or -1

    Let scan be 0
    Let current_line be 0

    While scan is less than doc_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, scan
        Note: Check for L=76
        If ch is equal to 76:
            If scan plus 3 plus name_len is less than doc_len:
                Let c1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, scan plus 1
                Let c2 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, scan plus 2
                Let c3 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, scan plus 3
                Note: "Let " = L(76) e(101) t(116) space(32)
                If c1 is equal to 101:
                    If c2 is equal to 116:
                        If c3 is equal to 32:
                            Let match be proc check_identifier_match with doc, scan plus 4, doc_len, name, name_len
                            If match is equal to 1:
                                Return current_line
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Set current_line to current_line plus 1
        End If
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    End While

    Return -1
End Process

Private Process called "find_process_declaration" takes doc as Integer, doc_len as Integer, name as Integer, name_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Search for 'Process called "<name>"' declaration, return line number or -1

    Let scan be 0
    Let current_line be 0

    While scan is less than doc_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, scan
        Note: P=80
        If ch is equal to 80:
            Note: Look for "Process called \"" (17 chars to the opening quote of name)
            If scan plus 17 plus name_len is less than doc_len:
                Let c1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, scan plus 1
                If c1 is equal to 114:
                    Note: Check if quoted name matches
                    Note: Skip to the opening quote position (scan + 16) and compare
                    Let quote_pos be scan plus 16
                    Let qc be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, quote_pos
                    If qc is equal to 34:
                        Let match be proc check_identifier_match with doc, quote_pos plus 1, doc_len, name, name_len
                        If match is equal to 1:
                            Return current_line
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Set current_line to current_line plus 1
        End If
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    End While

    Return -1
End Process

Private Process called "find_type_declaration" takes doc as Integer, doc_len as Integer, name as Integer, name_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Search for 'Type called "<name>"' declaration, return line number or -1

    Let scan be 0
    Let current_line be 0

    While scan is less than doc_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, scan
        Note: T=84
        If ch is equal to 84:
            If scan plus 14 plus name_len is less than doc_len:
                Let c1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, scan plus 1
                If c1 is equal to 121:
                    Note: "Type called \"" = 13 chars to quote position
                    Let quote_pos be scan plus 13
                    Let qc be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, quote_pos
                    If qc is equal to 34:
                        Let match be proc check_identifier_match with doc, quote_pos plus 1, doc_len, name, name_len
                        If match is equal to 1:
                            Return current_line
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Set current_line to current_line plus 1
        End If
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    End While

    Return -1
End Process

Private Process called "find_constant_declaration" takes doc as Integer, doc_len as Integer, name as Integer, name_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Search for "Constant <name> as" declaration, return line number or -1

    Let scan be 0
    Let current_line be 0

    While scan is less than doc_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, scan
        Note: C=67
        If ch is equal to 67:
            If scan plus 9 plus name_len is less than doc_len:
                Let c1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, scan plus 1
                Note: o=111
                If c1 is equal to 111:
                    Let match be proc check_identifier_match with doc, scan plus 9, doc_len, name, name_len
                    If match is equal to 1:
                        Return current_line
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Set current_line to current_line plus 1
        End If
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    End While

    Return -1
End Process

Private Process called "check_identifier_match" takes doc as Integer, start_pos as Integer, doc_len as Integer, name as Integer, name_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if the bytes at start_pos in doc match the identifier name
    Note: Returns 1 if match, 0 if not

    If start_pos plus name_len is greater than doc_len:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than name_len:
        Let doc_byte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, start_pos plus idx
        Let name_byte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with name, idx
        If doc_byte is not equal to name_byte:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Private Process called "check_word_boundary" takes doc as Integer, pos as Integer, word_len as Integer, doc_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if the identifier at pos is a complete word (not part of a larger word)
    Note: Checks character before pos and character after pos+word_len
    Note: Returns 1 if word boundary confirmed, 0 if part of larger word

    Note: Check character before the word
    If pos is greater than 0:
        Let before_ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, pos minus 1
        Let before_ident be proc is_identifier_char from before_ch
        If before_ident is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Note: Check character after the word
    Let after_pos be pos plus word_len
    If after_pos is less than doc_len:
        Let after_ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, after_pos
        Let after_ident be proc is_identifier_char from after_ch
        If after_ident is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Private Process called "create_symbol_info" takes name as Integer, kind as Integer, file_path as Integer, line as Integer, col as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a SymbolInfo structure (40 bytes)

    Let sym be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 40
    If sym is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let loc be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 32
    If loc is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with sym
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dummy_fp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with loc, 0, file_path
    Let dummy_ln be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with loc, 8, line
    Let dummy_cl be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with loc, 16, col
    Let dummy_el be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with loc, 24, line

    Let dummy_name be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with sym, 0, name
    Let dummy_kind be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with sym, 8, kind
    Let dummy_loc be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with sym, 16, loc
    Let dummy_container be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with sym, 24, 0
    Let dummy_detail be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with sym, 32, 0

    Return sym
End Process

Private Process called "extract_quoted_name" takes doc as Integer, start as Integer, doc_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract a quoted name from text starting at position
    Note: Scans for first quote, extracts text until closing quote
    Note: Returns newly allocated string, or 0

    Let scan be start
    Let quote_start be -1

    While scan is less than doc_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, scan
        If ch is equal to 34:
            If quote_start is equal to -1:
                Set quote_start to scan plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Note: Found closing quote - extract the name
                Let name_len be scan minus quote_start
                If name_len is greater than 0:
                    If name_len is less than 256:
                        Let name_buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with name_len plus 1
                        If name_buf is not equal to 0:
                            Let idx be 0
                            While idx is less than name_len:
                                Let byte_val be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, quote_start plus idx
                                Let dummy_cp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with name_buf, idx, byte_val
                                Set idx to idx plus 1
                            End While
                            Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with name_buf, name_len, 0
                            Return name_buf
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Private Process called "extract_word_after" takes doc as Integer, start as Integer, doc_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract a word (identifier) starting at the given position
    Note: Returns newly allocated string, or 0

    If start is greater than doc_len:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let word_end be start
    While word_end is less than doc_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, word_end
        Let is_ident be proc is_identifier_char from ch
        If is_ident is equal to 0:
            Set word_end to word_end plus doc_len
        Otherwise:
            Set word_end to word_end plus 1
        End If
    End While
    If word_end is greater than doc_len:
        Set word_end to word_end minus doc_len
    End If

    Let word_len be word_end minus start
    If word_len is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If word_len is greater than 255:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with word_len plus 1
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than word_len:
        Let byte_val be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, start plus idx
        Let dummy_cp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, idx, byte_val
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While
    Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, word_len, 0

    Return buf
End Process

Private Process called "extract_quoted_string_after" takes doc as Integer, start as Integer, doc_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract a quoted string starting at or after the given position
    Note: Delegates to extract_quoted_name

    Return proc extract_quoted_name with doc, start, doc_len
End Process

Private Process called "extract_line_text" takes doc as Integer, doc_len as Integer, target_line as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract the full text of a line for hover information
    Note: Returns newly allocated string containing the line text

    Let line_start be proc find_line_start with doc, target_line
    If line_start is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Find line end
    Let line_end be line_start
    While line_end is less than doc_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, line_end
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Set line_end to line_end plus doc_len
        Otherwise If ch is equal to 0:
            Set line_end to line_end plus doc_len
        Otherwise:
            Set line_end to line_end plus 1
        End If
    End While
    If line_end is greater than doc_len:
        Set line_end to line_end minus doc_len
    End If

    Let line_len be line_end minus line_start
    If line_len is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If line_len is greater than 1024:
        Set line_len to 1024
    End If

    Let buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with line_len plus 1
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than line_len:
        Let byte_val be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc, line_start plus idx
        Let dummy_cp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, idx, byte_val
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While
    Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, line_len, 0

    Return buf
End Process

Private Process called "get_keyword_hover" takes name as Integer, name_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if the identifier is a Runa keyword and return hover documentation
    Note: Returns pointer to documentation string, or 0 if not a keyword

    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let first_ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with name, 0

    Note: Check common keywords by first character and length
    Note: "Let" (3 chars, L=76)
    If first_ch is equal to 76:
        If name_len is equal to 3:
            Let doc_str be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 48
            If doc_str is not equal to 0:
                Note: "Let - Variable declaration"
                Note: L=76 e=101 t=116 space=32 -=45 space=32
                Note: V=86 a=97 r=114 i=105 a=97 b=98 l=108 e=101
                Let dummy1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 0, 76
                Let dummy2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 1, 101
                Let dummy3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 2, 116
                Let dummy4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 3, 32
                Let dummy5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 4, 45
                Let dummy6 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 5, 32
                Let dummy7 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 6, 68
                Let dummy8 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 7, 101
                Let dummy9 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 8, 99
                Let dummy10 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 9, 108
                Let dummy11 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 10, 97
                Let dummy12 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 11, 114
                Let dummy13 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 12, 101
                Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_str, 13, 0
                Return doc_str
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Private Process called "fuzzy_match_query" takes symbol_name as Integer, query as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Perform a fuzzy match of query against symbol name
    Note: Returns 1 if the query is a subsequence of the symbol name, 0 otherwise
    Note: If query is equal to 0 or empty, matches everything

    If query is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let first_query_byte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with query, 0
    If first_query_byte is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    If symbol_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Subsequence match: each character in query must appear in order in symbol_name
    Let qi be 0
    Let si be 0
    Let max_len be 256

    While qi is less than max_len:
        Let qch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with query, qi
        If qch is equal to 0:
            Note: All query chars matched
            Return 1
        End If

        Note: Find this query char in remaining symbol name
        Let found be 0
        While si is less than max_len:
            Let sch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with symbol_name, si
            If sch is equal to 0:
                Note: End of symbol name without matching all query chars
                Return 0
            End If

            Note: Case-insensitive comparison
            Let lower_q be qch
            Let lower_s be sch
            If lower_q is greater than 64:
                If lower_q is less than 91:
                    Set lower_q to lower_q plus 32
                End If
            End If
            If lower_s is greater than 64:
                If lower_s is less than 91:
                    Set lower_s to lower_s plus 32
                End If
            End If

            If lower_q is equal to lower_s:
                Set found to 1
                Set si to si plus 1
                Set si to si plus max_len
            Otherwise:
                Set si to si plus 1
            End If
        End While
        If si is greater than max_len:
            Set si to si minus max_len
        End If

        If found is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set qi to qi plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Private Process called "measure_string_len" takes str_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Measure length of null-terminated string
    If str_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let len be 0
    Let max_len be 1048576
    While len is less than max_len:
        Let byte_val be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with str_ptr, len
        If byte_val is equal to 0:
            Return len
        End If
        Set len to len plus 1
    End While
    Return len
End Process
